Library for practising PHP kata http://codekata.pragprog.com/

Requires
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
PHP 5.3+

Usage
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Running the kata.php file in the project's root directory (php -f kata.php) will 
collect all classes from the /Kata/Katas directory and run any methods therein against 
the test suite set-up for the class.

Please see the example class /Kata/Katas/BinSearch.php

Advanced Usage
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
If you wish to run only a single class you can specify the class name in the
command line like this:

php kata.php BinSearch 
------------Class-^ 

If you then want to limit the class to only a single method add this also:

php kata.php BinSearch binSearchRecursive
------------Class-^ -----Method-^
